1 aircraft system for educational, research, or testing purposes.
2 (6)[(5)] No law enforcement agency, or agent thereof, shall use an unmanned aircraft
3 system to conduct a search unless authorized under the Fourth Amendment to the
4 United States Constitution and Section 10 of the Kentucky Constitution. If the
5 search is conducted pursuant to a warrant, the warrant shall specifically authorize
6 the use of an unmanned aircraft system.
7 (7)[(6)] Except as limited by subsection (6)[(5)] of this section, any government
8 agency, including a law enforcement agency, may use an unmanned aircraft system
9 for legitimate governmental purposes.
10 (8)[(7)] When an unmanned aircraft system is used by law enforcement pursuant to
11 subsections (6)[(5)] and (7)[(6)] of this section, it shall be operated in a lawful
12 manner and shall minimize data collection on nonsuspects. Disclosure of such data
13 shall be prohibited except by order of a court of competent jurisdiction.
14 (9)[(8)] No evidence obtained or collected as the result of the use of an unmanned
15 aircraft system shall be admissible as evidence in any civil, criminal, or
16 administrative proceeding within this state for the purpose of enforcing state or
17 local law, except for:
18 (a) Evidence collected as permitted by subsections (3)[(2)] to (7)[(6)] of this
19 section; or
20 (b) Evidence which is offered against the owner or operator of an unmanned
21 aircraft system to show misconduct.
22 (10)[(9)] No law enforcement agency shall be required to operate unmanned aircraft
23 systems.
24 (11)[(10)] Operation of an unmanned aircraft system in violation of subsection (3)[(2)]
25 or (4)[(3)] of this section shall be a violation for the first offense and a Class B
26 misdemeanor for the second or subsequent offense.
27 (12) A person operating an unmanned aircraft system pursuant to subsections (3) to
