1 (5) of this section shall not use an unmanned aircraft system to record an image
2 of privately owned real property or of the owner, tenant, occupant, invitee, or
3 licensee of such property with the intent to conduct surveillance on, or publish
4 unauthorized images of, the individual or property captured in the image in
5 violation of the person's reasonable expectation of privacy. For purposes of this
6 subsection, a person is presumed to have a reasonable expectation of privacy on
7 his or her privately owned real property if he or she is not observable by persons
8 located at ground level in a place where they have a legal right to be, regardless
9 of whether he or she is observable from the air with the use of an unmanned
10 aircraft system.[(11) This section may be cited as the "Citizens' Freedom from
11 Unwarranted Surveillance Act."]
12 SECTION 2. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 411 IS CREATED TO
13 READ AS FOLLOWS:
14 The owner, tenant, occupant, invitee, or licensee of privately owned real property may
15 initiate a civil action in a court of competent jurisdiction against any person, agency,
16 or political subdivision that violates Section 1 of this Act and may seek:
17 (1) Appropriate injunctive relief;
18 (2) Actual damages;
19 (3) Punitive damages;
20 (4) Court costs; and
21 (5) Reasonable attorney's fees.
22 SECTION 3. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 413 IS CREATED TO
23 READ AS FOLLOWS:
24 An action filed pursuant to Section 2 of this Act shall be commenced within seven (7)
25 years after the cause of action accrued.
